text = "Nolaki are the people that practice life magic/shapeshifters
Nolaki worship first man as he gave them the gift of life but they give him a different name
also inhabited by the bouldaaks

Gildred is like 150 years old, she travels around the world, seeking powerful people that she can empower
she uses life magic and taps the soul to help her empower people

Soul rememebers the animals it transforms into so descendant can transform into animals it hasn't seen
capable of creating Soulstone, maybe only elders and the only \"country\" that can
so the Creation of Life is Soulstone
but in the Creation process you need an actual Soul it's weird like that

3 Nolaki tribes, 1 is a buff woman with 4 arms, 1 is a tree man with tree skin, and the last is a swordsman who eats souls into his sword using domination

The Greatfather which has lived ever since the First Man is the First Disciple of Life, he's just an old guy. Big tree in the middle which has Aura over the whole island, and if he detects a threat he can block it out.

**TIMELINE**
before first man - baulandians chilling
first man leaves (year 0) - other disciples go and explore other continents, nolak stays

some times within 50 years - Nolkains be making artifcats and forced to throw them away, some chase and settle in Pustan

some time between 50-100 - marutol wrecks havoc on bauland"
